
[1]gregarious

   GREGA'RIOUS, a. [L. gregarius, from grex, a herd.]

   Having the habit of assembling or living in a flock or herd; not
   habitually solitary or living alone. Cattle and sheep are gregarious
   animals. Many species of birds are gregarious. Rapacious animals are
   generally not gregarious.
